<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Lust1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Lust,</orth> subst. 1) pleasure, delight: <cit><quote>gazing upon the Greeks with little l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1384" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1384</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>whose eyes do never give but through l. and laughter,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.492" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 492</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) desire: <cit><quote>I'll answer to my l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 4.4.134" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 4, 134</bibl></cit> (I'll do at pleasure). Plur. <emph>--s</emph> == inordinate desires: <cit><quote>nor my --s burn hotter than my faith,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 34</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>polluted with your --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.43" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 4, 43</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>there serve your --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.1.130" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 1, 130</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>our unbitted --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.335" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 335</bibl></cit>.
